DESCRIPTION:<p>Mark your calendar for our Wednesday\, March 4 community mee
 ting at 7:00 PM at Good Shepherd Center. We have two important presentation
 s — a Seattle Tree Code overview from a certified arborist\, and an update 
 on the Lincoln Athletic Field at Lower Woodland Park\, presenting community
 -proposed alternatives to Seattle Public Schools' current plan.</p><p>We al
 so have significant breaking news: Seattle City Council has announced the P
 hase 2 Select Committee Meeting Schedule\, running March 19 through June 18
 \, 2026. This process will determine rezoning for Neighborhood Residential 
 lots facing bus corridors citywide — including key areas in Wallingford and
  Tangletown. Details are below\, and we will keep you updated as this moves
  forward.</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20260226T205205Z
LOCATION:Good Shepherd Center\, Room 202\, 4649 Sunnyside Ave N\, Seattle\,
  WA 98103\, USA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Wallingford Community Council Community Meeting
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
