DESCRIPTION:<p><strong>Community Update: Full-Size Athletic Field Site Anal
 ysis at Woodland Park</strong></p><p><strong>Date:</strong> <span dir="ltr"
 >Thursday\, November 6\, 2025</span> (Date Change)</p><p><strong>Time:</str
 ong> <span dir="ltr">6:30 pm</span></p><p><strong>Location:</strong> Lincol
 n High School Gymnasium\, entrance on <a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/cMB2
 Nar7RofeQM1V7" target="_blank">Woodlawn Avenue N near N 44th Street</a></p>
 <p>Seattle Public Schools is exploring Woodland Park as a potential site fo
 r a new full-size synthetic turf field. This could provide a longer-term so
 lution for Lincoln High School’s athletics needs while also serving youth s
 ports and community recreation.</p><p>For updates and project details\, vis
 it the <a href="https://www.seattleschools.org/departments/capital-projects
 -and-planning/school-construction/projects/lincoln-field/">project page</a>
 .</p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20251029T192145Z
LOCATION:Lincoln High School Theater\, Wallingford\, Seattle\, WA 98103\, U
 SA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Community Update: Full-Size Athletic Field Site Analysis at Woodlan
 d Park
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
