CREATED:20250502T001602Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>This <strong><b>free\, all-ages event</b></strong> celebrate
 s the beginning of summer with a <strong><b>community potluck picnic</b></s
 trong>\, <strong><b>flower headdress making</b></strong>\, <strong><b>child
 ren's crafts and games</b></strong>\, <strong><b>live music</b></strong>\, 
 and of course — a joyful <strong><b>dance around the Maypole</b></strong>. 
 No RSVP needed!</p><p><strong><b>Please bring a dish to share for the potlu
 ck!</b></strong><br> Vegan and gluten-free options are especially appreciat
 ed so everyone can enjoy the feast.</p><p></p><p>The celebration also featu
 res <strong><b>costume performances</b></strong>\, <strong><b>three Maypole
  dances</b></strong>\, and lively musical sets from the fabulous <em>Ricky 
 Gene and the Return of the Deadgrass</em>\, a <strong><b>community drum cir
 cle</b></strong> led by <em>Carold Nelson</em>\, and a <strong><b>family-fr
 iendly drum circle</b></strong> with <em>Jamtown John</em>.</p><p><em>Both 
 drummers are featured artists in the Rhythm Tent at NW Folklife!</em></p><h
 2>Schedule of Events</h2><p><strong><b>1:00–2:00 PM:</b></strong> Drum Circ
 le Welcome – <em>Carold Nelson</em></p><p><strong><b>2:00–3:00 PM:</b></str
 ong> Family Drum Circle – <em>Jamtown John Hayden</em></p><p><strong><b>3:0
 0–4:0</b></strong>0 <strong><b>PM:</b></strong> <em>Ricky Gene &amp\; the R
 eturn of the Deadgrass</em></p><p><strong><b>3:00–3:20</b></strong> <strong
 ><b>PM</b></strong>: Children’s Maypole Dance</p><p><strong><b>4:00–4:20</b
 ></strong> <strong><b>PM:</b></strong> Community Maypole Dance</p><p><stron
 g><b>4:00–5:00</b></strong> <strong><b>PM:</b></strong> Drum Circle – <em>C
 arold Nelson</em></p><p><strong><b>5:00–6:30</b></strong> <strong><b>PM:</b
 ></strong> <em>Ricky Gene &amp\; the Return of the Deadgrass</em></p><p><a 
 href="https://fremontartscouncil.org/may-day">https://fremontartscouncil.or
 g/may-day</a><em><br></em></p>
LAST-MODIFIED:20250502T001723Z
LOCATION:Meridian Playground\, 4920 Meridian Ave N\, Seattle\, WA 98103\, U
 SA
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Fremont Arts Council May Day Event
TRANSP:OPAQUE
END:VEVENT
