UID:1vibe33u77s6065n83i32m3ssq@google.com
CREATED:20251015T232946Z
DESCRIPTION:<p>Friday night\, October 10\, through Monday morning\, October
  13\, will mark the first of six weekends of southbound lane reductions to 
 finish drainage improvements.</p><p>In full\, southbound I-5 Ship Canal Bri
 dge lane reduction weekends will be:</p><p>• October 10–13<br>• October 17–
 20<br>• October 31–November 3<br>• November 21–24<br>• December 5–8<br>• Ja
 nuary 9–12</p><p>During this work\, southbound I-5 across the Ship Canal Br
 idge from about NE 45th Street to the SR 520 interchange will be reduced to
  two lanes. In general\, lane reductions will begin as early as 10 pm on Fr
 idays and all lanes will be reopened by 5 am on Mondays.</p><p>During these
  weekends\, express lanes will run southbound 24/7. So if you’re heading no
 rth\, just know that lanes won’t flip. Prepare for some delay there.</p><br
 ><a href="https://www.wallyhood.org/2025/10/six-weekends-of-southbound-i-5-
 lane-reductions/#gsc.tab=0">https://www.wallyhood.org/2025/10/six-weekends-
 of-southbound-i-5-lane-reductions/#gsc.tab=0</a>
LAST-MODIFIED:20251018T193851Z
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Southbound I-5 Ship Canal Bridge Lane Reductions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
END:VEVENT
